id: pm-lg65
title: "PR #240 review: applied vs declined Gemini findings (with rationale)"
description: "APPLIED: config.ts set --value drop (value: valueValue ?? options.value); init.ts invalid-preset undefined (?? 'minimal'); reindex.ts dead name guard removed via ?? providerName fallback; register-mutation.ts deps String(undefined)->'undefined' replaced with 'as string'. DECLINED (false positives): help-json-payload.ts:177 — the preceding loop only pushes options where (alias_for && long) are truthy, so 'as string' is safe and the suggested guard would be uncoverable dead code; comments.ts:71 — reached only when typeof options.file==='string' (hasFile branch), so the cast is guaranteed and a ?? '' guard would be dead; verify-published-release.mjs:31 — Node permits Atomics.wait on the main thread (unlike browsers), so the current synchronous-sleep idiom is correct and does NOT throw; item-format.ts:396 — coerceRuntimeFieldValue always throws an Error with a message, the non-Error arm is theoretical; item-format.ts firstNonZeroComparison lazy-eval — declined: would add 19 arrow-functions requiring fabricated cascading-tie fixtures across 16 fields to satisfy the 100% function gate, for negligible real perf on tiny bounded sort keys (conflicts with the lean-suite goal)."
type: Decision
status: closed
priority: 2
